      <div class="headerTittle">
        East Link
        <span>Melbourne, VIC</span>
      </div>
      <div class="projectDetail">
        <p>VLC first became involved in the EastLink project during the 1990s when it was known as the Scoresby Freeway. VLC produced travel demand modelling results for three separate studies:</p>
        <ul class="ullist">
          <li><span>Scoresby Corridor/Freeway Feasibility Study</span>
          </li>
          <li><span>Scoresby Corridor Environmental Impact Assessment</span>
          </li>
          <li><span>Scoresby Corridor Integrated Transport Study/Business Planning</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>The project was not intended to be financed by tolls at this time, and VLC was responsible for justifying the project purely on economic grounds.</p>
        <p>VLC was again engaged in the early 2000s when the Victorian State Government began exploring the possibility of delivering EastLink by a PPP mechanism with tolls. This work involved the production of traffic and revenue forecasts for different project configurations, tolling strategies and toll levels. This included undertaking extensive 'revealed preference surveys' in 2003 that explored how route choice was being influenced by tolls on the already operational CityLink toll road. VLC used this data to calibrate state-of-the art toll diversion curves that forecast the degree to which people in Melbourne will avoid taking a toll under differing time saving/toll charge scenarios.</p>
        <p>This results of this work suggested that a viable PPP project could be put to market. The EastLink toll road opened in 2008 and continues to operate successfully. VLC's traffic and toll revenue forecasts for EastLink were only 1 per cent higher than demand that eventuated after ramp up. The bidders' forecasts were 30 per cent higher than actual.</p>
        <p>The toll diversion relationships developed by VLC for EastLink have since been used to closely predict traffic and toll revenue for both the Cross-City Tunnel and Lane Cove Tunnel in Sydney, and Airport Link and the Clem7 tunnel in Brisbane.</p>
      </div>

